# 125. Valid Palindrome

## Approach

1. Use two pointers, one starting from the beginning and the other from the end of the string.
2. Skip all characters that are not letters or digits.
3. Convert both characters to lowercase before comparing them.
4. If the characters are different, return false.
5. If the characters are the same, move both pointers toward the center.
6. Continue until the pointers meet or cross.
7. If no mismatch is found, return true.

## Time Complexity

O(n)

Where:

*  n = Length of the input string.

Each character is visited at most once while moving the two pointers.

## Space Complexity

O(1)

No extra data structures are used. Only a few variables are maintained.

